    <item>
      <title>How to Fit the FreeBSD Logo in a Perfect Circle</title>
      <link>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2026/how-to-fit-the-freebsd-logo-in-a-perfect-circle/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 12:00:00 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2026/how-to-fit-the-freebsd-logo-in-a-perfect-circle/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The FreeBSD and Apple logos are quite similar. &lt;br/&gt;&#xA;Both have a heavy base and leaves / tails on top.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2026/how-to-fit-the-freebsd-logo-in-a-perfect-circle/apple-freebsd-wrong-circle-fit.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Apple and FreeBSD logos compared by their heavy base and top detail, followed by a wrong circular crop approach&#34; width=&#34;928&#34; height=&#34;200&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; decoding=&#34;async&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;br/&gt;&#xA;&lt;br/&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;this-is-how-apple-fits-its-logo-into-a-circle&#34;&gt;This is how Apple fits its logo into a circle&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2026/how-to-fit-the-freebsd-logo-in-a-perfect-circle/apple-homepod-logo.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Apple logo centered on the circular top surface of a black HomePod&#34; width=&#34;1472&#34; height=&#34;980&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; decoding=&#34;async&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;br/&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;With guides:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2026/how-to-fit-the-freebsd-logo-in-a-perfect-circle/apple-homepod-circle-guides.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Apple HomePod top with orange circular guides around the speaker surface and Apple logo&#34; width=&#34;1472&#34; height=&#34;980&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; decoding=&#34;async&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Why I Ditched Dark Mode on macOS</title>
      <link>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2025/why-i-ditched-dark-mode-on-macos/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 07 Sep 2025 22:42:50 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2025/why-i-ditched-dark-mode-on-macos/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://interfacecraft.online/blog/2025/why-i-ditched-dark-mode-on-macos/image.webp&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; width=&#34;956&#34; height=&#34;282&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; decoding=&#34;async&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I stopped using dark mode on my macOS. I don&amp;rsquo;t need it anymore. It actually creates more problems than it solves.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The original idea was good: with dark mode in the operating system, you can use your computer at night without damaging your eyes with high brightness. Dark mode was first introduced in macOS Mojave in 2018. Then web community realized the same need. In 2019, the CSS Working Group added new specifications for prefers-color-scheme. This means that any website can specify colors for dark mode.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
